<Layout title="Security Patch - Authentication" description="Critical authentication vulnerability fix">
  <h1>Security Patch – Authentication Vulnerability</h1>

  <h2>Issue</h2>
  <p>A critical security vulnerability was discovered in the authentication system that could potentially allow unauthorized access under specific conditions.</p>

  <h2>Resolution</h2>
  <p>Implemented enhanced authentication checks and session validation. Updated all authentication endpoints to use secure token verification.</p>

  <h2>Impact</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Eliminates potential unauthorized access vulnerability.</li>
    <li>Strengthens overall system security posture.</li>
    <li>Ensures compliance with security best practices.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Technical Changes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Enhanced JWT token validation logic.</li>
    <li>Implemented additional session state verification.</li>
    <li>Added rate limiting for authentication endpoints.</li>
    <li>Updated security documentation and guidelines.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Recommendations</h2>
  <p>All users are encouraged to log out and log back in to refresh their authentication tokens. System administrators should review access logs for any suspicious activity.</p>

  <hr>

  <p><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}bugfixes/`}>← Back to Bug Fixes</a> | <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Home</a></p>
</Layout>
